HEADWORD: kazoo
<hw>ka*zoo"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Etymol.
uncertain.]</ety> <def>A kind of toy or rude musical instrument, as a
tube inside of which is a stretched string or membrane made to vibrate
by singing or humming into the tube.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

